cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on improving the accuracy of deep neural networks in image classification and instance segmentation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a learning-based frequency selection method, which involves analyzing the spectral bias from a frequency perspective. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper leverages identical structures of well-known neural networks, indicating that it may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to reducing input data size, which may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
